{
  "name": "Pufferfish",
  "type": "ancestry",
  "effects": [],
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "gm": "",
      "value": "<p>Your companion is a pufferfish, a round fish that can inflate its body and is covered in sharp spines.</p><p><strong>Size</strong> Small</p><p><strong>Melee</strong> <span class=\"pf2-icon\">1</span> spines (finesse), Damage 1d6 piercing plus poison</p><p><strong>Str</strong> +2, <strong>Dex</strong> +3, <strong>Con</strong> +1, <strong>Int</strong> –4, <strong>Wis</strong> +1, <strong>Cha</strong> +1</p><p><strong>Hit Points</strong> 4</p><p><strong>Skill</strong> Intimidation</p><p><strong>Senses</strong> low-light vision</p><p><strong>Speed</strong> swim 35 feet</p><p><strong>Special</strong> The pufferfish's spines attack deals an additional 1d4 poison damage or 2d4 poison damage if the pufferfish is a specialized companion.</p><p><strong>Support Benefit</strong> Your pufferfish inflates, thrusting its spines into your enemies. Until the start of your next turn, your Strikes that damage a creature in your pufferfish's reach also deal 1d6 persistent poison damage. If your pufferfish is nimble or savage, the persistent poison damage increases to 2d6.</p><p><strong>Advanced Maneuver</strong> @UUID[Compendium.pf2e-animal-companions.sf-AC-Advanced-Maneuvers.Item.HpqgfV5ZBxjCKnuN]{Barbed Dash}</p>"
    },
